Simple LOC counter for different languages, shows a pie chart and some stats.

The GUI requires:

- Python 2.6+
- WxPython http://www.wxpython.org/

To run:

    pyloc.py

To run in console mode, which just outputs the stats:

Usage: pylocstats.py directory [-v]

Where directory is the directory to scan and -v will cause verbose output.

Example basic output:
---------------------

[james@collingwood pyloc]$ ./pyloc.py /home/james/projects-git/haskellhead/ 

    PYLOC
    -----
    Folder   : /home/james/projects-git/haskellhead/

    Summary
    -------
    Haskell: 99.04%
    Shell: 0.96%

    TOTAL physical SLOC : 1,775

Example verbose output:
-----------------------

    [james@collingwood pyloc]$ ./pylocstats.py -v ../haskellhead/
    
    PYLOC
    -----
    Folder   : ../haskellhead/
    
    Shell (1 files) :
            Code       : 12
            Comments   : 1
            Whitespace : 4
    
            Physical SLOC : 17
    
    C (1 files) :
            Code       : 20
            Comments   : 5
            Whitespace : 5
    
            Physical SLOC : 30
    
    Haskell (16 files) :
            Code       : 1,349
            Comments   : 150
            Whitespace : 288
    
            Physical SLOC : 1,787
    
    
    Summary
    -------
    Haskell: 97.44%
    C: 1.64%
    Shell: 0.93%
    
    TOTAL physical SLOC : 1,834
